# Amazon Scraper

A lightweight web application that scrapes Amazonâ€™s first page of search results for a given keyword and displays each productâ€™s title, star rating, number of reviews and thumbnail in a clean, responsive interface.

**Repository**  
<https://github.com/Dred2215/Trainee-Test.git>

---

ğŸš€ Features

- **Live search**: enter any term and see real-time results from Amazon.
- **Product cards**: display title, rating, reviews and image.
- **Responsive layout**: grid of cards adjusts to any screen size.
- **Fast backend**: powered by Bun + Express + Axios + JSDOM â€” no headless-browser overhead.
- **Dev proxy**: Vite proxies `/api` calls to avoid CORS.
- **Error handling**: user-friendly messages on network or parsing errors.

---

ğŸ—ï¸ Architecture & Logic

# Backend (Bun + Express)

1. **Server**  
   - Express serving HTTP routes  
   - CORS enabled for cross-origin requests from the frontend

2. **Scraping**  
   - **Axios** fetches `https://www.amazon.com/s?k=<keyword>` with a real-browser User-Agent  
   - **JSDOM** parses the HTML into a `document`  
   - Selects `div[role="listitem"][data-component-type="s-search-result"]` for each product  
   - Extracts:
     - **Title**: text inside `<span>` or `aria-label` on `<h2>`  
     - **Rating**: first token of `.a-icon-alt` (e.g. â€œ4.5â€)  
     - **Reviews**: numeric text in `span.a-size-base.s-underline-text`, stripped of punctuation  
     - **Image**: `src` of `img.s-image`  
   - Returns an array of `{ title, rating, reviews, image }`

3. **API routes**  
   - `GET /api/scrape?keyword=<term>` â†’ array of product objects  
   - (Optional) `GET /api/count?keyword=<term>` â†’ `{ count: <number> }`

# Frontend (Vite + Vanilla JS)

1. **Vite config**  
   - Proxies `/api` â†’ `http://localhost:3000` to bypass CORS during development

2. **Modules**  
   - `src/api.js`: `fetchResults(keyword)` wraps `fetch('/api/scrape?...')`  
   - `src/components/productCard.js`: `createProductCard(item)` builds each card element  
   - `src/main.js`: orchestrates input â†’ fetch â†’ render  

3. **Styles**  
   - Amazon-inspired palette (blue header, yellow buttons)  
   - Responsive grid, hover/focus states, loading spinner

